CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 2, 1960, pg. A3 reads: "Y-Phalanx Award Winners - The fourth annual banquet of the Y-Phalanx Fraternity was held on March 27 at the Centre Avenue YMCA. Following the etsablished [sic] custom, awards were given to members for outstanding services performed.  in left photo Donald McCreary, primas, is shown after he presented plaques to three members for outstanding services in the community and to the YMCA.  They are Mrs. Delores Wilson, adviser to the Y-Gradale Sorority; Atty. Byrd R. Brown and the Rev. Cornell E. Talley of Central Baptist Church...-Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Donald McCreary, presenting community services plaques to Delores Wilson, Atty. Byrd R. Brown, and Rev. Cornell E. Talley during Y-Phalanx Fraternity banquet, Centre Avenue YMCA
